ate]]\n! Mintage<ref name=\"circulation\"/>{{efn|name=mintage}}\n|-\n| 1st\n| \u5143\n| 2019\n| 58,614,000\n|-\n| 2nd\n| \u4e8c\n| 2020\n| TBD\n|-\n|}\n\n==Commemoratives==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Image\n! class=\"unsortable\"| [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]\n! [[Gregorian calendar|Gregorian date]]\n! Mintage\n! Reason\n|-\n| [[File:100yen-S39Olympic.jpg|100px]]\n| align=\"center\"| \u4e09\u5341\u4e5d (39)<br>Sh\u014dwa{{efn|39th year of [[Emperor Sh\u014dwa]] (Hirohito)'s reign, [[Emperor Heisei]] ([[Akihito]]) was not crowned emperor until 1989}}\n| align=\"center\"| 1964\n| align=\"center\"| 80,000,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ngccoin.com/price-guide/world/japan-100-yen-y-79-yr.39-1964-cuid-1131923-duid-1442917|title=Japan 100 Yen Y# 79 Yr.39/1964|publisher=[[Numismatic Guaranty Corporation]]|accessdate=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| [[1964 Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"LOC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mof.go.jp/english/currency/coin/commemorative_coins/list.htm#other|title=Commemorative Coins List|work=[[Ministry of Finance (Japan)]]|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Banpaku100.jpg|100px]]\n| align=\"center\"| \u56db\u5341\u4e94 (45)<br>Sh\u014dwa\n| align=\"center\"| 1970\n| align=\"center\"| 40,000,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ngccoin.com/price-guide/world/japan-100-yen-y-83-yr.451970-cuid-1133222-duid-1443554|title=Japan 100 Yen Y# 83 Yr.45(1970) |publisher=Numismatic Guaranty Corporation|accessdate=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| [[Expo 70]] in [[Osaka]]<ref name=\"LOC\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:SapporoOlympic100.jpg|100px]]\n| align=\"center\"| \u56db\u5341\u4e03 (47)<br>Sh\u014dwa\n| align=\"center\"| 1972\n| align=\"center\"| 30,000,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ngccoin.com/price-guide/world/japan-100-yen-y-84-yr.47-1972-cuid-1202593-duid-1442952|title=Japan 100 Yen Y# 84 Yr.47/1972|publisher=Numismatic Guaranty Corporation|accessdate=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| [[1972 Winter Olympics]] in [[Sapporo]]<ref n